<h2>Requesting a resale certificate (unit sales &amp; transfers)</h2>
<p>When a unit owner other than the declarant sells or transfers a unit, Texas Property Code <a href="https://statutes.capitol.texas.gov/?tab=1&amp;code=PR&amp;chapter=PR.82&amp;artSec=82.157" target="_blank" rel="noopener">§82.157 (Resale of Unit)</a> requires the Association to furnish a current <strong>resale certificate</strong> — including the Association's operating budget and the statutorily required statements of assessments and unpaid amounts, fees, reserves, capital expenditures, judgments and pending suits, insurance, and known violations. Owners, listing agents, and title companies can request that certificate (and a statement of the seller's account) using the button below.</p>
<p><a class="btn" href="{{ site.forms.resaleRequest }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Request a resale certificate / statement of account →</a></p>
<p class="note">A statutory fee applies (capped by Tex. Prop. Code <a href="https://statutes.capitol.texas.gov/?tab=1&amp;code=PR&amp;chapter=PR.82&amp;artSec=82.157" target="_blank" rel="noopener">§82.157</a>); the certificate is prepared within the three-month currency window the statute requires.</p>

<div class="callout statute">
  <p style="margin:0"><span class="k">About this page.</span> <a href="https://statutes.capitol.texas.gov/?tab=1&amp;code=PR&amp;chapter=PR.82&amp;artSec=82.116" target="_blank" rel="noopener">§82.116</a> requires the Association to record a management certificate and to make its dedicatory instruments available to members. <a href="https://statutes.capitol.texas.gov/?tab=1&amp;code=PR&amp;chapter=PR.82&amp;artSec=82.1142" target="_blank" rel="noopener">§82.1142</a> contemplates a member-accessible website. This page and the <a href="/governing-documents/">Governing Documents</a> page serve that member-accessible function. The recorded certificate on file with Hays County, and the copy in the Texas Real Estate Commission's database at <a href="https://www.hoa.texas.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">hoa.texas.gov</a>, are the official versions.</p>
</div>
